TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gratton, Gabriele
AU  - Holden, Richard
AU  - Kolotilin, Anton
T1  - When to Drop a Bombshell
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdx070
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 85
IS  - 4
SP  - 2139
EP  - 2172
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Sender, who is either good or bad, wishes to look good at an exogenous deadline. Sender privately observes if and when she can release a public flow of information about her private type. Releasing information earlier exposes to greater scrutiny, but signals credibility. In equilibrium bad Sender releases information later than good Sender. We find empirical support for the dynamic predictions of our model using data on the timing of U.S. presidential scandals and U.S. initial public offerings. In the context of elections, our results suggest that October Surprises are driven by the strategic behaviour of bad Sender.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdx070
ER  - 



